Step 1: Let's simplify the expressions in the parentheses.
\begin{align}
(\cos12^\circ+i\sin12^\circ+\cos48^\circ+i\sin48^\circ)^6&=
(\cos12^\circ)\space^6+\space
(i\sin12^\circ)\space^6+\space
(\cos48^\circ)\space^6+\space
(i\sin48^\circ)\space^6\\
&=
cos12^\circ\space^6+sin12^\circ\space^6+cos48^\circ\space^6+sin48^\circ\space^6
\end{align}

Step 2: Convert the real parts to polar form.
\begin{align}
cos12^\circ\space^6+sin12^\circ\space^6+cos48^\circ\space^6+sin48^\circ\space^6&=\left| ⟂ + \sqrt{⟁}⋅⟂ \right|^6=⟂^6=ω^6\\
ω&=\frac{⟂²--⟁²}{\sqrt{⟁⋅⟂}}\in ℝ.
\end{align}

Step 3: Evaluate the real parts and find the imaginary parts.
\begin{align}
ω^6&=i⟂^3ζ²⟁ζ⟂,⟂=cos12^\circ,⟁=sin12^\circ,⟂=1/⟂,ζ=cos48^\circ\\
&=32π^2i\left(\cos12^\circ\sin48^\circ+\sin12^\circ\cos48^\circ+\cos12^\circ\cos48^\circ \right)
\end{align}

