Let's rearrange the equation to make $x$ the subject:
\begin{align*}
\log_8 (\log_2 x)= \log_8 x &= 3,\\
\log_2 (\log_8 x) &= \frac{3}{8},\\
\log_2 x &= \frac{9}{8},\\
x &= \frac{512}{64},\\
\boxed{(\log_2 x)^2 = 8\cdot 512}
\end{align*}
Now, we can use the property $(\log_2 x)^2 = x$ to find the result:
\begin{align*}
\boxed{(\log_2 x)^2 = \boxed{(\log_2 x )\cdot (\log_2 x)}} &= 8\boxed{512 \cdot \frac{512}{512}} = \boxed{4096},\\
\end{align*}

